[1] Michigan (Grand Traverse County)
Date: Thu 18 Dec 2014
Source: MLive [edited]
http://www.mlive.com/news/grand-rapids/index.ssf/2014/12/whooping_cough_outbreak_in_gra.html


The pertussis outbreak in Grand Traverse County [Michigan] has reached 70 confirmed cases, plus 14 cases of a similar disease, called parapertussis, according to the health department. Students at 19 schools in the county have been affected by the disease, also known as whooping cough. The county health department has received 3750 calls to the hotline set up to field questions from parents of children who may have been exposed to the illness.

As they announced the update on the outbreak on Thu 18 Dec 2014, health officials urged residents to get vaccinated in advance of holiday travel and get-togethers. "Preventing severe disease and death in infants is our highest priority," said Wendy Trute, the Grand Traverse health officer. "We urge all pregnant women to get vaccinated. We also urge parents to vaccinate infants as soon as possible."

A pertussis outbreak was reported in November 2014 at Grand Traverse Academy, a charter school. The number of confirmed cases linked to the school remains at 12, said Mike Lahey. He did not have numbers on the cases in the Traverse City Area Public School District.

[byline: Sue Thoms]

