[3] Nebraska (Dodge, Saunders and Washington counties)
Date: Tue 16 Dec 2014
Source: The Republic, Associated Press report [edited]
http://www.therepublic.com/view/story/9a0752fa5c6841d5b249fa8064de1f5c/NE--Eastern-Nebraska-Illnesses


An eastern Nebraska health department is reporting several cases of whooping cough. The Fremont Tribune reports that Three Rivers Health Department in Fremont says at least 2 cases of whooping cough have been confirmed in the district, which includes Dodge, Saunders and Washington counties.

Whooping cough, or pertussis, is spread when infected people cough or sneeze. It starts like the common cold and can progress into violent coughing spells.

