[7] New Mexico (Valencia County)
Date: Wed 17 Dec 2014
Source: KRQE [edited]
http://krqe.com/2014/12/17/school-district-warns-parents-of-whopping-cough/


A New Mexico school district is warning parents about whooping cough. Los Lunas schools [Valencia County] sent emails to parents and even called them saying there have been several cases of pertussis, or whooping cough, in the area.

Health officials say whooping cough tends to hit in waves. In New Mexico in 2012, there were nearly 900 cases. In 2013 there were more than 600; so far in 2014 there were about 300.

