[The increase in the number of cases of pertussis in the past few years in the USA is likely multifactorial, although in part due to the wave-like nature of the disease over years it is clear that the acellular vaccine, which is much better tolerated in children and can be given to adults, does not protect against _Bordetella pertussis_ as long. There is also some evidence that recent clonal strains have toxins that are less antigenic similar to the vaccine strain. - Mod.LL

